commit_message:
Allow role defaults to determine the branch tested

Currently there's an override in place to make the tests
use the master branch. This becomes a pain when master
becomes a stable branch because this override is out of
the norm, so it gets forgotten.

The override is not necessary - we can just use the
values from the role defaults instead.

Change-Id: I4cf8a97ee93da9e2648cc47782e6984ab7cc13b7

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Includes backport of https://review.openstack.org/475371

Change-Id: If6de7e83330b7e44e0e58e34e4eeb976ce6e7d84

commit_message:
Separate rsyslog image definition

This separates the rsyslog image definition into a server image
"rsyslog" and an "rsyslog-base" image. This will enable the creation of
more finegrained images depending on the use-case, e.g.: A minimal
side-car container image that merely outputs what it gets from syslog to
stdout.

Change-Id: I33ae15c0beb5af6179a84f3722150a287316ad25

commit_message:
use l3 api def from neutron-lib

Commit I81748aa0e48b1275df3e1ea41b1d36a117d0097d added the l3 extension
API definition to neutron-lib, commit
I2324a3a02789c798248cab41c278a2d9981d24be rehomed the l3 exceptions and
Ifd79eb1a92853e49bd4ef028e7a7bd89811c6957 shims the l3 exceptions in
neutron.

This patch consumes the l3 API definition from neutron-lib
in prep for If2e66e06b83e15ee2851ea2bc3b64ad366e675dd

Change-Id: I17dbc5833cb80cd0b9476f0e4943c6ae19681b9a

commit_message:
[upstream] Remove agenda from slides

As we decided to be flexible with the agenda and organizing the blocks
the agenda in the slides is no longer accurate. This patch removes the
two slides with the agenda that we will edit on the training etherpad
during the introductions section.

Change-Id: I252a4d243e946e297c85ac53edf99c5936f0e91b

commit_message:
added level of indirection causes incorrect hiera config

 - until Newton this worked fine, however starting with Ocata, we
   do not need the key 'mapped_data'
 - having it results in extra indirection in the dictionary in
   neutron_bigswitch_data.json

Closes-Bug: #1729453

Change-Id: I3bc9940aeff4e290d83de95a7df294c11f061954
(cherry picked from commit 485339129cee8f5d3223cf47858a5c9f79b0a8de)

commit_message:
Increase the Mistral RPC timeout

Some actions can take more than 60 seconds. If they are executed
directly this results in a messaging timeout. We are doubling the
default to be safe.

Change-Id: Idb315912152ff7e30fa8750698e9bad59da88fce
Related-Bug: #1719333

commit_message:
[DNM] Setup Tempest for tripleo-common

NOTE: This code will eventually land in a new repo called
tripleo-common-tempest-plugin as per the Tempest Queens goal[1].
However, to avoid any delays while that is setup it will continue to
live in this review so that it can be updated and worked on easily.

[1]: https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/queens/split-tempest-plugins.html

Change-Id: I8607c858160a5809941bee565e384b9ef929662e

commit_message:
Fix missing domain arguments in functional tests

After a recent fix to tempest to allow specification of
project and user domains in the cliclient [1] our functional
tests fail because we leave these with "" as value rather
than None when these arguments are not supplied.
Change the following parameters to None if there is no value
when we init the manila cliclient:

project_domain_name
project_domain_id
user_domain_name
user_domain_id

[1] I50490428f85e264e6b5e3b7c83ff768a986cb8c8

Closes-bug: #1729795
Change-Id: Iedde7a4a674a60e760b17d1eb2973f42d79223d2

commit_message:
Remove log translations

Log messages are no longer being translated.
This removes all use of the _LE, _LI, and _LW translation markers
to simplify logging and to avoid confusion with new contributions.

See:
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-i18n/2016-November/002574.html
http://lists.openstack.org/pipermail/openstack-dev/2017-March/113365.html

Change-Id: I1d66f85a3981c4cc633f7c809c5065e9cf1f7c50

commit_message:
Allow object versioning by default

Object versioning is necessary to pass DefCore test suite,
i.e. allows Kolla version of OpenStack to be certified
as "OpenStack Powered Platform".

Change-Id: Id5003f7fe2aebdeffe1cf7ce1b6177a6bca8f5b6
Co-Authored-By: Alexander Reunov <alexander.reunov@oracle.com>
Closes-Bug: #1729583

commit_message:
Migrate to session for glance client

As the general patch of migration to using keystoneauth
Sessions was introduced and merged, the work is not completed
for glance service only.

This finishes migration to Sessions for image service.

There is a specific case here when glance service needs
to maintain two cases: keystone and noauth strategies.
Previously glance client required endpoint, token and
SSL options. For now for keystone the session will have
all needed ,srameters but still custom endpoint should be
generated firstly and if not succeeded session may try to
get glance endpoint. In the case of keystone the certificate
file is taken from auth config options, otherwise options
`[glance]/glance_cafile` and `[glance]/glance_api_insecure`
are taken.

Change-Id: Ia7c8925c78cf27d3b24308541c4757bbddc4c48d

commit_message:
'all' parameter breaks task context

The previous context of task is injected in the current task when contains 'all' operation.
For example, the expression function 'task' no longer works.

Change-Id: I04a0e7e7a2b8d37346c1aadfad8d7a6b972abcbe
Closes-Bug: 1705394
Signed-off-by: Vitalii Solodilov <mcdkr@yandex.ru>

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-05 23:21:57.000000000', 'message': 'Implement power_off/power_on for the FakeDriver

When trying to recreate hundreds of instance action
events for scale testing with the FakeDriver, a nice
simple way to do that is by stopping those instances

commit_message:
Implement power_off/power_on for the FakeDriver

When trying to recreate hundreds of instance action
events for scale testing with the FakeDriver, a nice
simple way to do that is by stopping those instances
and starting them again.

However, since power_off/on aren't implemented, once
you "stop" them the sync_instance_power_state periodic
task in the compute manager thinks they are still running
on the "hypervisor" and will stop them again via the API,
which records yet another instance action and set of
events.

This just toggles the power state bit on the fake instance
in the FakeDriver to make the periodic task do the right
thing.

As a result, we also have more realistic API and
notification samples.

Change-Id: Ie621686053ad774c4ae4f22bb2a455f98900b611

commit_message:
Remove unnecessary comment

Convertion from Quota object to dict was marked to be
deleted when OpenStack SDK will be at least in version 0.9.12.
Now SDK is in version 0.9.19 but it still retuns Quota object
instead of dict so convertion is still necessary and it
will be like that so this comment is not needed anymore.

Change-Id: I328beba6930f38c279884dbb0e67f2e022076cb1

commit_message:
Switch pacemakerized Cinder services to containerized variants in scenarios

The main environment files already reference containerized
pacemakerized Cinder services, but the scenarios still need to switch
from non-containerized to containerized.

Related-Bug: #1712070

commit_message:
Decoupling of Mistral tempest test from Mistral code base

The Mistral Tempest tests have a hard-coded dependency on Mistral being present
when Tempest tests are executed.
When trying to sparse-checkout the mistral_tempest_tests folder to run
the Mistral tests as a Tempest plugin; it fails due to Mistral not
being installed as some utilities and resources which are written in
the Mistral Tempest tests are being hard referenced from Mistral
being installed in the same environment.

This patch decouples the Mistral Tempest Tests so that they can be executed in
a stand-alone mode along with the necessary resources that are required to
execute the Tempest tests.

Change-Id: Ifd6a3a65a14c4ad4736dccc3e72cd564b6f53a0a

commit_message:
Register default pools and health policies in code

This commit uses the existing policy-in-code module to move all
default policies for pools and health into code. This commit also adds
helpful documetation about each API those policies protect,
which will be generated in sample policy files.

commit_message:
Do not parse updated_at for task if it was not updated

Currently if we try to get task from db, that was not updated yet
we get an error like:

YaqlEvaluationException: Can not evaluate YAQL expression
[expression=task().result.content, error='NoneType' object has no
attribute 'isoformat', data={}]

So we need to check if updated_at attr is not None, and do not force
parsing the attribute.

Change-Id: I7d5a068bd217c826891402a94da0a588beee8547
Closes-bug: #1729685

commit_message:
Reorder checks in apply_filters in db/_model_query

Function _kwargs_to_filters() in objects/db/api.py creates a filter
dictionary where all the values are made iterables except in the case
of StringMatchingFilterObj objects. As a consequence, when processing
such a filter, function apply_filters() in db/_model_query.py must
check if a value is a StringMatchingFilterObj before assuming it is
an iterable.

Change-Id: I1b43a06f6e35eaa61c6e6770076a167e6ee83987
Closes-Bug: #1724177

commit_message:
Give cinder user admin role

According to the documentation [1], the cinder user should be given the
admin role rather than the service role in the service project, just
like the other OpenStack services.

[1] https://docs.openstack.org/cinder/pike/install/cinder-controller-install-ubuntu.html

This patch lets the segmentation_id 0 pass through.

Closes-bug: 1718385

Initially the intent for adding this was to better test
any patches for roles together before they merge, but it

commit_message:
Remove unified queue from gate pipeline

Initially the intent for adding this was to better test
any patches for roles together before they merge, but it
has had the unintended side-effect of causing patches to
take much longer to merge (because they all get lined up
in a single queue, rather than independent queues) and
a lot more infra resources are used (because a patch
that fails at the top of the queue will result in all
subsequent patches restarting all their tests).

As discussed in the channel, we'd prefer to revert back
to the previous independent queue method of testing. It
has served us well.

Change-Id: If45fbcaae3f0bd467c2d569e3b0dca14d373e108

commit_message:
Use zuul v3 src location to install ARA

With zuul v3 the ARA git clone will be there if
the test is executed by the ARA repo, or if there
is a depends-on patch from ARA. This allows us to
simplify the conditional.

Change-Id: Id76b2084b1ba8df7bfddd4fbb4b0cbe9859fd849
(cherry picked from commit 5667c17b1bf8210c8f98b08f6a7675c87ca257c6)

commit_message:
Use new gnocchi repo URL

The gnocchi project has moved out of openstack to
an independent repo in github. The role should use
that URL as a default to ensure that any updates
to the branch are included.

Change-Id: I8f85d0ddca0f069de050df76ca334157c17cf0c8

Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

Zuul now supports including the file extension on the playbook path

to include the extension.

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-31 12:25:45.000000000', 'message': "Fix iptables rules override bug in clustercheck docker service

When deploying a composable HA overcloud with a database role split off
to separate nodes we could observe a deployment failure due to galera
never starting up properly.

The reason for this was that instead of having the firewall rules for
the galera bundle applied (i.e. those with the extra control-port for
the bundle), we would see the firewall rules for the BM galera service.
E.g. we would see the following on the host:

tripleo.mysql.firewall_rules: {
  104 mysql galera: {
    dport: [ 873, 3306, 4444, 4567, 4568, 9200 ]

Instead of the correct mysq bundle firewall rules:
tripleo.mysql.firewall_rules:
  104 mysql galera-bundle:
    dport: [ 873, 3123, 3306, 4444, 4567, 4568, 9200 ]

The reason for this is the following piece of code in
https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-heat-templates/blob/master/docker/services/pacemaker/clustercheck.yaml#L62:
...
  MysqlPuppetBase:
    type: ../../../puppet/services/pacemaker/database/mysql.yaml
    properties:
      EndpointMap: {get_param: EndpointMap}
      ServiceData: {get_param: ServiceData}
      ServiceNetMap: {get_param: ServiceNetMap}
      DefaultPasswords: {get_param: DefaultPasswords}
      RoleName: {get_param: RoleName}
      RoleParameters: {get_param: RoleParameters}

outputs:
  role_data:
    description: Containerized service clustercheck using composable services.
    value:
      service_name: clustercheck
      config_settings: {get_attr: [MysqlPuppetBase, role_data, config_settings]}
logging_source: {get_attr: [MysqlPuppetBase, role_data, logging_source]}
...

Depending on the ordering of the clustercheck service within the role
(before or after the mysql service), the above code will override the
tripleo.mysql.firewall_rules with the wrong rules because we derive from
puppet/services/... which contain the BM firewall rules.

Let's just switch to derive from the docker service so we do not risk
getting the wrong firewall rules during the map_merge.

Tested this change successfully on a composable HA with split-off DB
nodes.

Change-Id: Ie87b327fe7981d905f8762d3944a0e950dbd0bfa
Closes-Bug: #1728918
"}]
commit_message:
Fix iptables rules override bug in clustercheck docker service

When deploying a composable HA overcloud with a database role split off
to separate nodes we could observe a deployment failure due to galera
never starting up properly.

The reason for this was that instead of having the firewall rules for
the galera bundle applied (i.e. those with the extra control-port for
the bundle), we would see the firewall rules for the BM galera service.
E.g. we would see the following on the host:

tripleo.mysql.firewall_rules: {
  104 mysql galera: {
    dport: [ 873, 3306, 4444, 4567, 4568, 9200 ]

Instead of the correct mysq bundle firewall rules:
tripleo.mysql.firewall_rules:
  104 mysql galera-bundle:
    dport: [ 873, 3123, 3306, 4444, 4567, 4568, 9200 ]

The reason for this is the following piece of code in
https://github.com/openstack/tripleo-heat-templates/blob/master/docker/services/pacemaker/clustercheck.yaml#L62:
...
  MysqlPuppetBase:
    type: ../../../puppet/services/pacemaker/database/mysql.yaml
    properties:
      EndpointMap: {get_param: EndpointMap}
      ServiceData: {get_param: ServiceData}
      ServiceNetMap: {get_param: ServiceNetMap}
      DefaultPasswords: {get_param: DefaultPasswords}
      RoleName: {get_param: RoleName}
      RoleParameters: {get_param: RoleParameters}

outputs:
  role_data:
    description: Containerized service clustercheck using composable services.
    value:
      service_name: clustercheck
      config_settings: {get_attr: [MysqlPuppetBase, role_data, config_settings]}
logging_source: {get_attr: [MysqlPuppetBase, role_data, logging_source]}
...

Depending on the ordering of the clustercheck service within the role
(before or after the mysql service), the above code will override the
tripleo.mysql.firewall_rules with the wrong rules because we derive from
puppet/services/... which contain the BM firewall rules.

Let's just switch to derive from the docker service so we do not risk
getting the wrong firewall rules during the map_merge.

Tested this change successfully on a composable HA with split-off DB
nodes.

Change-Id: Ie87b327fe7981d905f8762d3944a0e950dbd0bfa
Closes-Bug: #1728918

commit_message:
Only mount Haproxy TLS if contents are set

For non-pacemaker deployments, this mounts the TLS certificate only if
it's actually going to be used.

Change-Id: Id8ba09902d25689e642f922c43e71649977bf248

commit_message:
Change developer_mode branch to newton-eol

Now that the service repo has been tagged EOL, the branch
no longer exists, so to allow the role to continue to be
deployed we should switch developer_mode to using it.

Change-Id: Id5546df0dc486f25bacf3eb7819ffda26fecc50d

commit_message:
Switch integration jobs to use local mirrors

The integration jobs currently download images from a third party
mirror which can be slow at times or use up a lot of bandwidth.

This patch tries to automatically detect if nodepool mirrors are
active and uses them, falling back to the global round-robin mirror
of the Fedora project instead of a specific mirror.

Change-Id: Ie111c20b6dd0efe2e1cbfcac2a46b27ce6bc20c0

commit_message:
Use 'project' instead of 'tenant' when switching to openstackclient
command

We tend to use 'project' rather than 'tenant' when switching to
openstackclient command, such as:

  openstack role add --user <user> --project <project> <role>

Change-Id: I87c82f49799714ccaf478a7305b1de8f5cb8281e

commit_message:
Deprecate policies API

The policies API should never be used. This marks it deprecated in
the API reference so that operators do not waste time looking at it.
It also logs a deprecation warning if the API is called.

Change-Id: I816997826e931a253777145e2c5f894e39182a8f

commit_message:
Return 404 on a GET if tombstone is newer

Currently the proxy keeps iterating through
the connections in hope of finding a success even
if it already has found a tombstone (404).

This change changes the code a little bit to compare
the timestamp of a 200 and a 404, if the tombstone is
newer, then it should be returned, instead of returning
a stale 200.

Closes-Bug: #1560574

Co-Authored-By: Tim Burke <tim.burke@gmail.com>
Change-Id: Ia81d6832709d18fe9a01ad247d75bf765e8a89f4
Signed-off-by: Thiago da Silva <thiago@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Add a new fiedl in pools or vol_stats

In some case the web developer will need this field by calling
cinder get-pools to find out whether the volume driver has enabled
image volume cache and to tell user further that it maybe spend
more time to create a volume from an image or the user could
create multi volume at the same time quickly and so on.
So I think it would be useful.

Change-Id: I6394b5162fe2f0178e5e871d4533a5ba7c104b01

[{'created': '2017-11-02 10:58:38.000000000', 'message': 'Add NetIpMap to hieradata for *ExtraConfig overrides

To enable per-node override of bind IPs via the per-role
ExtraConfig paramaters, we need to enable hiera interpolation
that references the keys defined in NetIpMap, so we add them
to the hieradata.  To minimise the risk of any conflicts in
keynames it's added near the bottom of the hierarchy, but
I'm not aware of any conflicting names in our templates/modules.

This will allow per-node hieradata override of bind IPs e.g:

    ComputeRack1ExtraConfig:

    ComputeRack2ExtraConfig:
      nova::vncproxy::host: "%{hiera('rack2_internal_api')}"

Change-Id: Icf7da1d78176c2ee0197ff2459d69d995cbb16ad
(cherry picked from commit 65a8b65754d2ea77ec2396658d4e73eb837d34bd)
'}]
commit_message:
Add NetIpMap to hieradata for *ExtraConfig overrides

To enable per-node override of bind IPs via the per-role
ExtraConfig paramaters, we need to enable hiera interpolation
that references the keys defined in NetIpMap, so we add them
to the hieradata.  To minimise the risk of any conflicts in
keynames it's added near the bottom of the hierarchy, but
I'm not aware of any conflicting names in our templates/modules.

This will allow per-node hieradata override of bind IPs e.g:

  parameter_defaults:
    ComputeRack1ExtraConfig:
      nova::vncproxy::host: "%{hiera('rack1_internal_api')}"
    ComputeRack2ExtraConfig:
      nova::vncproxy::host: "%{hiera('rack2_internal_api')}"

Closes-Bug: #1726884
Change-Id: Icf7da1d78176c2ee0197ff2459d69d995cbb16ad
(cherry picked from commit 65a8b65754d2ea77ec2396658d4e73eb837d34bd)

commit_message:
Providing required priviledges to the mounted NFS volume

Since, user ID on host and container differs, image-create
with NFS backend was failing with permission error. But even after
resolving permission error[1] the image was not getting created
on the nfs share as the NFS endpoint is not mounted successfully on
the container via puppet. This will be fixed by [2].

Now, adding two below changes in this patch,
[1]. chown glance:glance /var/lib/glance.
[2]. Proposing this solution to mount NFS endpoint on the host instead
     of mounting it on glance container, because mounting in container
     does not work as explained in LP Bug.

Closes-Bug: 1708629
Change-Id: Ib60cb0d179e7c117dc26440746154136aa9d163e
(cherry picked from commit
ed11f8ebcfbaf1fbbebb4c83e3201e462fee14ee)

commit_message:
Update CephPools format in the docker templates to fit ceph-ansible

The format which ceph-ansible uses to describe the list of pools
to be created in the cluster is different from the one which
puppet-ceph uses; this commit updates the description and the
the docker templates accordingly.

Change-Id: I1e5b2c3cbf6ae02c19a2275ca119fed6e173319d
Closes-Bug: #1720373
(cherry picked from commit c10aa7a0439fb7d8e8e964e75d73f3cbb54aa9ec)

commit_message:
Modify error message encountered during stack update

Parameters of an existing stack can be updated with
openstack stack update <stack> --existing --parameter <parameter>=<newvalue>
Example : openstack stack update stack1 --parameter p1=v1
If the --existing option is skipped, it leads to the below error
Need to specify exactly one of --template-file, --template-url or --template-object
This error is misleading as the user might think that stack update
cannot be performed without specifying a new template.

Modify the error message with --existing option.

Change-Id: Idce88bde848378e00b1c873245600ba205939668
Closes-Bug: #1723864

commit_message:
Move legacy ironic-lib jobs in-tree

This patch moves the legacy ironic-lib CI jobs into the ironic-lib
tree instead of storing them in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs
to give us control as we migrate the legacy jobs to the new ansible
roles.

Change-Id: Id9b0c22b73135ca0e9a952e909e8295550ad899f

commit_message:
Use assertIsNone(...) instead of assertIs(None,...)

Following OpenStack Style Guidelines: [1]
Unit test assertions tend to give better messages for
more specific assertions. As a result, assertIsNone(...)
is preferred over assertIs(None, ...)

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/hacking/#unit-tests-and-assertraises

Change-Id: Ibd179f48bc014c502b9c50f7ff59b4d48cbcbc51

commit_message:
Add missing job to gate

The job ironic-tempest-dsvm-ipa-wholedisk-bios-agent_ipmitool-tinyipa
is done in the check queue, but wasn't being done in gate. This adds
it to gate.

To make it easier to detect mismatches between the jobs in check vs
gate, the jobs are reordered so that they are in the same order in
check and gate, and the non-voting ones are grouped together.

Change-Id: Ic3d2571394be0e2b1eb73c044e1aea0ecdd3c864

commit_message:
Move legacy ironic-lib jobs in-tree

This patch moves the legacy ironic-lib CI jobs into the ironic-lib
tree instead of storing them in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs
to give us control as we migrate the legacy jobs to the new ansible
roles.

Change-Id: Id9b0c22b73135ca0e9a952e909e8295550ad899f
(cherry picked from commit 5ab2d5c67a60078eb34ccd6fb28fcc90d0247a11)

commit_message:
Fix AssertionError in test_rand_password_with_len_2

This commit fixes the AssertionError in test_rand_password_with_len_2.
We were thinking an error could be happened but it's really rare.
However, it was actually happened[1]. To make the test more stable,
we shouldn't check its value but only length. It should be enough
because we already checked values in the other test cases.

[1] http://paste.openstack.org/show/625330/

Change-Id: I9a11a56e5eee9d1b01b61c04ea4bc75037c4458e

First, setting config name inside RedisAdmin initialization sounds more reasonable. As for getting wrong config command name, rebuilding admin client can help solve it. And what if you just add a little bit of code inside get_config_command_name(), e.g: renamed_cmds = self.configuration_manager.get_value('rename-command') or [], then add config_name into RedisAdmin initialization, you can always get correct config name whenever building admin client."}, {'account_id': 13157, 'date': '2017-11-02 03:47:48.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

Yes, this is another issue. As Fan Zhang mentioned in the comment, when requirepass modified by configuration group management, RedisAdmin should also be updated.'}, {'account_id': 23540, 'date': '2017-11-02 04:26:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5:

The purpose of the patch is updated config_name after building admin client. As Fan Zhang mentioned in the comment, if we add config_name into RedisAdmin initialization, then it must call get_config_command_name() in the _build_admin_client(),like https://review.openstack.org/#/c/516250 did. But in terms of code readability, i think it is confused to put a redis management command in the process of building admin client.'}, {'account_id': 13157, 'date': '2017-11-02 05:24:14.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1

> The purpose of the patch is updated config_name after building
 > admin client. As Fan Zhang mentioned in the comment, if we add
 > config_name into RedisAdmin initialization, then it must call
 > get_config_command_name() in the _build_admin_client(),like
 > https://review.openstack.org/#/c/516250 did. But in terms of code
 > readability, i think it is confused to put a redis management
 > command in the process of building admin client.

get_config_command_name is not a redis management command, it's a method of RedisApp and only read a configuration from configuration manager. set_config_command_name is a method of RedisAdmin, when we need to change the RedisAdmin object we could call this method. But this is not the case we have to change the RedisAdmin object, as config command was not changed during the RedisAdmin object lifecycle. The config command is mangled during Redis deployment, so we should always construct a RedisAdmin object with the correct config command at the beginning.

So I votes for https://review.openstack.org/#/c/516250 ."}, {'account_id': 21049, 'date': '2017-11-03 01:05:22.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

if you think jian song's patch is better, so I abandon this patch, so as to fix the bug as soon as possible."}]

commit_message:
Fix redis apply configuration failed after trove-guestagent restarted

For safe operation, trove-guestagent start redis with setting "CONFIG" command
to a mangled config command name. trove-guestagent service saved this mangled
config command in memory while preparing redis datastore by applying initial
guestagent configuration.But after restarted, trove-guestagent rollback the
config command to the original name "CONFIG", which was considered as a illegal command.
this patch aims to fix the problem.

Change-Id: I9457f982dcdcf4cbd10211325aaec69780ca9ed9
Closes-Bug: #1726341

commit_message:
Increase oslo.context minimum version to 2.19.2

There was a bug introduced by the oslo.context 2.19.1 release for
projects that were overriding the Context from_dict function in an
incompatible way.  To avoid this happening in the future, we made
some improvements to the base from_dict so consumers wouldn't have
to override it at all.  However, in order for those projects to
begin relying on that behavior they need to know they have a new
enough version of oslo.context.  2.19.2 is that version.

Change-Id: I64bc760c5c2c34b1e3cc0441dc8c468131b49682
Related-Bug: 1721432

commit_message:
Deprecate mod_fastcgi. Promote civetweb.

puppet-apache has dropped support for fastcgi on RHEL/CentOS 7 hosts (1).
This patch deprecate fastcgi for removal in the P+2 release. Civetweb
is set a the default frontend for rgw.

Change-Id: I8681018ccd9d38df5e964385d6d433c42c246b06
1: https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-apache/commit/6c1ed75df6988dee291041c1bc4251f0f9525be9

commit_message:
Drop pyflakes from the test requirements

pyflakes is being pulled in in the right version by hacking,
so let that one be installed upfront and remove explicit
dependencies on pyflakes (which is anyway only called via
flake8 which is pulled in by hacking)

commit_message:
Disable kvm on OVH infra instances

OVH infra hosts are causing "KVM: entry failed, hardware error 0x0"
failures where instances fail to start (cirros, etc.).
This patch excludes OVH instances from kvm enablement until the issue is
resolved.

(cherry picked from commit 283c7baf3251558b8bf1f0b48e43c2befe80648d)

Change-Id: Ic1712be01268b8f63290e1ea00c6f7e14a244558

commit_message:
Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

Zuul now supports including the file extension on the playbook path
and omitting the extension is now deprecrated.  Update references

[{'created': '2017-10-04 15:20:33.000000000', 'message': 'Fix Horizon asset compression not happening on redeploy

A recent change to kolla-ansible (a729dcc4) bind mounts /tmp from the
host to handle uploading of larger images. Unfortunately this is also
where we keep the state file for horizon which controls whether assets
need to be recompressed (.local_settings.md5sum.txt). This means it is
left over on destroy and causes issues with CSS / assets on redeploy.

Change the location of this file to

along with the container.

commit_message:
Fix Horizon asset compression not happening on redeploy

A recent change to kolla-ansible (a729dcc4) bind mounts /tmp from the
host to handle uploading of larger images. Unfortunately this is also
where we keep the state file for horizon which controls whether assets
need to be recompressed (.local_settings.md5sum.txt). This means it is
left over on destroy and causes issues with CSS / assets on redeploy.

Change the location of this file to
/var/lib/kolla/.local_settings.md5sum.txt so it is cleaned up correctly
along with the container.

Change-Id: Icfc71266cabedc2c1a3d30590cada3f774bc0d2c
Closes-Bug: #1721281

commit_message:
Add support for "per_volume_gigabytes" and "backup_gigabytes" quota

Update a testcase "test_update_all_quota_resources_for_tenant" to verify
"per_volume_gigabytes" and "backup_gigabytes" quota updating.

Note: There is a bug in api v2 documentation[1], since "backup_gigabytes"
      and "per_volume_gigabytes" parameters aren't mentioned in api v2
      document, although they are supported.

[1] https://bugs.launchpad.net/openstack-api-site/+bug/1727631

Change-Id: I9b6aa355f7a5b7fb6836e377c0f374707402c977

[{'created': '2017-11-02 16:54:11.000000000', 'message': "Correct mac generation block

The block/rescue we were using in the mac generation task did not work
as expected. Because we use an iterator on the task and we can't iterate
over the entire block the task would fail when mac address lookups
within a running container didn't already exist but needed to be
created. This resulted in the task failing for a single host and being
removed from the inventory instead of running a rescue for only the
missing network.

The use of block/rescue has been removed. If the feature to loop over a
block is ever implemented [0] we can revisit how this action is done.

[0] - https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/13262
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

Change-Id: Ie4bc3b130874047a5cbd36b98ed86a731ae5c317
"}]
commit_message:
Correct mac generation block

The block/rescue we were using in the mac generation task did not work
as expected. Because we use an iterator on the task and we can't iterate
over the entire block the task would fail when mac address lookups
within a running container didn't already exist but needed to be
created. This resulted in the task failing for a single host and being
removed from the inventory instead of running a rescue for only the
missing network.

The use of block/rescue has been removed. If the feature to loop over a
block is ever implemented [0] we can revisit how this action is done.

[0] - https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/13262
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

Change-Id: Ie4bc3b130874047a5cbd36b98ed86a731ae5c317

commit_message:
Disable kvm on OVH infra instances

OVH infra hosts are causing "KVM: entry failed, hardware error 0x0"
failures where instances fail to start (cirros, etc.).
This patch excludes OVH instances from kvm enablement until the issue is
resolved.

(cherry picked from commit 283c7baf3251558b8bf1f0b48e43c2befe80648d)

Change-Id: Id9fd686f90013504b97ebcf9ffc08556f1ca125d

commit_message:
FQDN validation

Adds optional validation to ensure FQDN set by Nova matches /etc/hosts
as created by overcloud heat configuration.

Consistent FQDN requires the nova parameter [Default]/dhcp_domain to
match the CloudDomain tht parameter.

This validation is disabled by default.

Change-Id: Ib5689acae66baf63ecccbc3b1c0b96684781b863
(cherry picked from commit bae2d113938b9bb22d4c291ae312d2299187f72b)
Partial-Bug: #1581472

Disable kvm on OVH infra instances

OVH infra hosts are causing "KVM: entry failed, hardware error 0x0"
failures where instances fail to start (cirros, etc.).

commit_message:
RHSM: when using proxy, test its connectivity first

When using RHSM with a proxy, we want to make sure the proxy can be
reached. This patch verify that a tcp socket can be open from the client
to the proxy.

This patch also does a bit of refactoring:
- --retry-delay 10 --max-time 30 is now used in a parameter everytime we
  use curl.
- proxy options are now used everytime curl is used, even for detecting
  which version of Satellite is running, now we use proxy options.

Co-Authored-By: Vincent S. Cojot <vincent@cojot.name>
Change-Id: I4dcac1528c10f698338383445e27c8a613f9bcd9
Closes-Bug: #1724970

commit_message:
Make nova patching parameters configurable in Nuage

Nova patching parameters are available in nova.conf but are not
configurable from tripleo-heat-templates. Exposing these parameters
from Nuage composable services to make them configurable. It enables
setting the patching parameters in environment files. This change
depends on the addition of nova patching configuration parameters.

Change-Id: Iacad25da044f2bac83ee5f577ddcd70650eb61e5
Depends-On: I51ef3e19daff1d98cfe5c2c16475c16e6a3e3e0f
(cherry picked from commit f0041153eca8d82bb7f72dc68676cab8448ef037)

commit_message:
Fix typos in container_images_prepare failure task names

The message tasks in case of failures should reference the task to
prepare the container images itself. In the case of create_plan, it
would return a message for the wrong task, and in the case of
update_plan I think it would fail altogether. This now references the
correct task name.

Change-Id: Ie05bd113b8c20ee95aef82b07c63a9591baab98a

commit_message:
os-net-config not run when conf is empty and re-introduce exception.

There may be cases where os-net-config is empty leading to issue when
we force the run during its special treatment in upgrade/update.

Piggy back in this review is re-adding the os-net-config special
handling to update and non-controller.  But it‚Äôs more robust now it
won‚Äôt run the command unconditionally, it needs:
 - os-net-config to be upgraded
 - /etc/os-net-config/config.json to exist and not be empty.

Another improvement is that it will prevent any networking cut during
its run as we are using the ‚Äìno-activate flag.

Change-Id: Ie1b88d5cac22fca5b0b325b1dd8c81d65b63acb8
Closes-Bug: #1728889

commit_message:
Fix using old Swift rings when creating a new stack

The container to store Swift rings is not deleted when the stack is
deleted. This results in re-deploying old rings when deploying a new
stack.

This patch creates a copy of the old rings with a timestamp suffix and
removes the original object. Doing this will create new rings when
creating a new stack.

Closes-Bug: 1671783
Change-Id: Ie6363987ada9b516064c1ed3b215f809c3924393
(cherry picked from commit f82064e95a60b63c0c6a1df92a70f33158bc1a18)

commit_message:
[upstream] Add slides on 'WIP' patches to Workflow

It was discussed after the class in Boston that we might want
to add something about 'Work In Progress' patches in the
workflow section somewhere.  After looking through the content the
best place to put it seemed to be in the 'Reviewing' section as
that allowed to tell how a 'WIP' could be indicated and then how
that should be handled from a review standpoint.

This patch adds a couple of slides to cover the topic.

Change-Id: Icf77b248e4cfddf1d6efd5fa1d8b0a94fefdc76d

[{'created': '2017-10-26 18:04:03.000000000', 'message': 'Always call iptables-restore with -w if done once

In the case where we called iptables-restore with a
-w argument and it succeeded, we should short-circuit
future calls to always use -w, instead of trying
without it, just to fall-back to using it on failure.

While analyzing some l3-agent log files I have seen
lots of "Perhaps you want to use the -w option?",
followed by a call with -w, followed by not using it
the next time. Changing this can save one failing
call to iptables-restore.

Change-Id: Icac99eb1d43648c64b6beaee0d6201f990eacb51
Related-bug: #1712185
(cherry picked from commit 6c50ad5858175e2eddeed7a3e28cf8b53c2eb2b3)
'}]
commit_message:
Always call iptables-restore with -w if done once

In the case where we called iptables-restore with a
-w argument and it succeeded, we should short-circuit
future calls to always use -w, instead of trying
without it, just to fall-back to using it on failure.

While analyzing some l3-agent log files I have seen
lots of "Perhaps you want to use the -w option?",
followed by a call with -w, followed by not using it
the next time. Changing this can save one failing
call to iptables-restore.

Change-Id: Icac99eb1d43648c64b6beaee0d6201f990eacb51
Related-bug: #1712185
(cherry picked from commit 6c50ad5858175e2eddeed7a3e28cf8b53c2eb2b3)

commit_message:
Change OVS agent to update skipped port status to DOWN

When the OVS agent skips processing a port because it was
not found on the integration bridge, it doesn't send back
any status to the server to notify it.  This can cause the
port to get stuck in the BUILD state indefinitely, since
that is the default state it gets before the server tells
the agent to update it.

The OVS agent will now notify the server that any skipped
device should be considered DOWN if it did not exist.

Conflicts:
 neutron/plugins/ml2/drivers/openvswitch/agent/ovs_neutron_agent.py

Change-Id: I15dc55951cdb75c6d87d7c645f8e2cbf82b2f3e4
Closes-bug: #1719011
(cherry picked from commit a789d23b0242ae3b4c13856e96a72a3acc5a3697)

commit_message:
Change OVS agent to update skipped port status to DOWN

When the OVS agent skips processing a port because it was
not found on the integration bridge, it doesn't send back
any status to the server to notify it.  This can cause the
port to get stuck in the BUILD state indefinitely, since
that is the default state it gets before the server tells
the agent to update it.

The OVS agent will now notify the server that any skipped
device should be considered DOWN if it did not exist.

Change-Id: I15dc55951cdb75c6d87d7c645f8e2cbf82b2f3e4
Closes-bug: #1719011
(cherry picked from commit a789d23b0242ae3b4c13856e96a72a3acc5a3697)

commit_message:
Remove fake_keystone

We now used Ansible (via 'config download') instead of the
os-collect config agent for local undercloud deployment.
This eliminates part of our Keystone dependencies...

This patch updates our heat.conf for the undercloud installer
so that it no longer requires a fake_keystone to be running
and instead uses a fake keystoneclient shim.

This patch also re-implements our event list code so that
rather than depend on openstackclient (which also
required the fake keystone API) we use heatclient's
library directly.

By a combination of the above we can eliminate use of
fake_keystone entirely and thus avoid spawning the
extra thread, socket, and associated cleanup.

Depends-On: I03f1789957ba157871fd13164592116d7fcdabe4
Depends-On: I5413ae4eadd5affdd1ae01678b61eafbe50b7919

Change-Id: Ic7a10a334b34190f406f05c4167c494a0092502b

commit_message:
Log additional info about entries

In order to pinpoint bugs better it's necessary to log more details
about the entries. The entry id will now be logged to better correlate
the entry processing.
Also dependencies will be logged to better understand if bugs in
dependency calculations exist.

Change-Id: I9078487bd4722132e92b48d7d333c93c82a002d9
Partial-Bug: #1713487

Make configuration files more readable

In order to make OpenStack configuration files written by Chef more
readable, this patch introduces a blank line before every section
heading.

commit_message:
Restrict launch fields when restoring from backup

When restoring from backup the launch wizard contains all options
and performs no customizations based on the information contained
in the backup.

This patch adds support for restricting the launch instance
datastore field to the datastore and datastore version that the
backup is relevant to.

It also populates the restored backup as the only option in the
advanced step backup field.

Added a unit test to validate the fields were populated correctly.

Change-Id: Iabfefd34b5f7a24699277104fa92ac77b2c74fe3
Closes-Bug: #1647746

commit_message:
Fix to use . to source script files

Refer to ``Code conventions`` at [1] for details.
When you have to source a script file, for example, a credentials file
to gain access to user-only or admin-only CLI commands,
use . instead of source.

[1] https://docs.openstack.org/contributor-guide/writing-style/code-conventions.html

Change-Id: Ie59c58662c85e22d5651cfc8891181b8dfeb07c9

commit_message:
Deprecated the V1 drivers

The V1 drivers are not actively maintained by the networking-odl team
for a few cycles already and aren't guaranteed to even work.
As such, the networking-odl team has decided [1] that the drivers will
be marked as deprecated beginning Queens cycle, and removed in the
beginning of the Rocky cycle.

commit_message:
Fix the wrong usage of new style class in metering

This problem will cause self.host to be overridden by cfg.CONF.host
instead of the passed host value when calling MeteringAgent.__init__(host).

Change-Id: I50c5136e1cf1eb0db28edd02129f963948a54741

'}]
commit_message:
Re-add keystone-manage credential_setup

The step that ran keystone-manage credential_setup has been removed
as "deprecated" with the "Initial identity Pike updates" [1].

However, the Pike CLI documentation for keystone-manage does not
indicate that the command is deprecated [2] and the install-guide
continues to use it [3].

Also, I got this error message on a Pike installation (Ubuntu):

ERROR keystone.common.fernet_utils [...] Either [credential] key_repository
does not exist or Keystone does not have sufficient permission to access
it: /etc/keystone/credential-keys/

For these reasons, this patch reinstates the keystone-manage
credential_setup step.

[1] commit 5279aa4fbc6e2885e86954105237c94d71890f20
    (Change-Id: I518ed83f7e19c590e7846160889faf46db274b3a)
[2] https://docs.openstack.org/keystone/pike/cli/index.html
[3] https://docs.openstack.org/keystone/pike/install/keystone-install-ubuntu.html

Change-Id: Iad5afd70ab99d968a6546bd19e5e5831a8299a49

commit_message:
Fix to use . to source script files

Adhering to coding conventions. Refer to ``Code conventions`` at
https://docs.openstack.org/contributor-guide/ for details.
When you have to source a script file, for example, a credentials file
to gain access to user-only or admin-only CLI commands, use . instead of source.
https://docs.openstack.org/contributor-guide/writing-style/code-conventions.html

Change-Id: Ie39797f2d84b757b9c27078ec0dc67b8229c676f

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Depends-On: I4f4cc284ab7d1c3378e01737f9fade3afe251824
Depends-On: If151501923c5308cfeaee6e33d12df3e7f6959d5

commit_message:
Fix meter-label-rule creation

The existing method is to meter outgoing traffic from the entire VM
to a specific "remote_ip_addr"(in case of outbound),
but the method I suggested can meter outgoing traffic
from a particular subnet to external network.

From a metering point of view,
it does not matter which address/CIDR is the destination for outbound.
But, it is important to know where(subnet or VM) the packet leaves from.
That way you can see how much VMs are using the external network.
For outbound metering, dst is 0.0.0.0/0 and src is network of VMs
and for inbound metering, src is 0.0.0.0/0 and dst is network of VMs.

When creating a meter-label-rule, it is correct
to specify src address for "remote_ip_prefix" option for outbound
and specify dst address for inbound.
If you are confused by the term "remote_ip_prefix",
you need to clarify this option.

Change-Id: I2f11ad0d80d83872b6ebc6129b865760900de30f
Closes-Bug: #1716913

commit_message:
fullstack: Remove ovsdb_interface config opt

ovsdb_interface option was deprecated [1]. Fullstack tests are
still not stable so removing tests using ovs-vsctl interface from
fullstack won't remove much of testing coverage but removal will
simplify the testing matrix a lot.

[1] Change Ieb2b8916d4cdbb3b7e6a953c827b176f2217a42f

Change-Id: I2655e403c2a63038035048a9ada985c471437367

revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-11 23:05:27.000000000', 'message': "Fix migration_get_in_progress_by_host_and_node status list

This DB API method is returning all in-progress migration
records for a given host and node.

It determines what is in-progress by filtering out migration
status values for things that mean NOT in progress.

There are a couple of issues with this:

1. 'accepted' is an in-progress starting state for evacuate
   and live migration operations.

2. 'done' is an end state for a successful evacuation, so it
   should be included in the list of things that are not in
   progress.

So this change removes 'accepted' from and adds 'done' to the
list of *not* in-progress states used for filtering in this method.

Change-Id: I294fb28d279979f6e3409f1530a553dd525e53da
"}, {'created': '2017-10-11 23:47:54.000000000', 'message': "Add 'done' to migration_get_in_progress_by_host_and_node filter

This DB API method is returning all in-progress migration
records for a given host and node.

It determines what is in-progress by filtering out migration
status values for things that mean NOT in progress.

However, 'done' is an end state for a successful evacuation,
so it should be included in the list of things that are not in
progress.

Change-Id: I294fb28d279979f6e3409f1530a553dd525e53da
"}]
commit_message:
Add 'done' to migration_get_in_progress_by_host_and_node filter

This DB API method is returning all in-progress migration
records for a given host and node.

It determines what is in-progress by filtering out migration
status values for things that mean NOT in progress.

However, 'done' is an end state for a successful evacuation,
so it should be included in the list of things that are not in
progress.

Change-Id: I294fb28d279979f6e3409f1530a553dd525e53da

commit_message:
Rework r10k verbose option

The command "r10k puppetfile install -v" fails with:
Unrecognized options: verbose.

Rework the command to be compatible with the r10k 1.1.4.

Closes-bug: #1707629

Change-Id: I05d888125284d2808fb248e52afc95ab2b948353
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bogdando@mail.ru>
(cherry picked from commit 885abd1ae0f604fae73fe262493d3b5598613cd0)

Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

Zuul now supports including the file extension on the playbook path
and omitting the extension is now deprecrated.  Update references
to include the extension.

commit_message:
Add some check for zuul.d/projects.yaml

Add framework to run checks on zuul.d/projects.yaml.

For now it checks that each project has the system-required template
and that zuul.d/projects.yaml is sorted.

Remove the file tools/zuul-projects_sorted.sh which did a sort test as
well.

Update list of repos so that they are in the order expected (bash and
python string comparison is different).

Change-Id: I29e0b7f49ec890f62d6c521e443248ab33cb819a
Depends-On: I19dbdebc1c02f0ae6ab6671b4cf3fb3c4382a820

commit_message:
Fix bug: Trove dashboard makes openstack dashboard not work.

It is caused by that: the DeleteConfiguration and DeleteParameter
class in database_configurations/tables.py must have both action_past
and action_present methods while they not.

Change-Id: I2596efdc974440d396e6788bc301c9a04982ba00
Closes-Bug: #1690003

commit_message:

Allow the configuration of image_member_quota
in Glance API. This error blocks the ability
of sharing images if the default value (128)
is reached.

commit_message:
RHSM: do not use retry to deploy katello-agent

katello-agent is an optional package, we don't want to use retry.
The package is available or not.

Fixing a regression from https://review.openstack.org/#/c/386529
Since we use "| true", we can't really use "retry" here.

Change-Id: Id8cd9ac54e158ee1743b2f72b169b3a066f69168
Closes-Bug: #1728614
(cherry picked from commit d9f7b01c6c21b306005bad12fcab103b0a9e7591)

commit_message:
migration: Superceed use of 'ceph mon rm'

Use the remove command (instead of rm) which is supported in
Ceph firefly or later (which covers all current deployment targets).

This resolves an issue with the ceph -> ceph-mon/ceph-osd migration
process for Luminous based deployments.

Change-Id: I127930e7c4b80465796b8270a9966b08f7c03037
Closes-Bug: 1729370

[{'created': '2017-10-30 16:55:51.000000000', 'message': "WIP: libvirt: do not remove inst_base when volume-backed during resize

When confirming a resize, the libvirt driver on the source host checks
to see if the instance base directory (which contains the domain xml
files, etc) exists and if the root disk image does not, it removes the
instance base directory.

However, the root image disk won't exist on local storage for a
volume-backed instance and if the instance base directory is on shared
storage, e.g. NFS, between the source and destination host, the
instance base directory is incorrectly deleted.

This adds a check to see if the instance is volume-backed when checking
to see if the instance base directory should be removed from the source
host when confirming a resize.

commit_message:
libvirt: do not remove inst_base when volume-backed during resize

When confirming a resize, the libvirt driver on the source host checks
to see if the instance base directory (which contains the domain xml
files, etc) exists and if the root disk image does not, it removes the
instance base directory.

However, the root image disk won't exist on local storage for a
volume-backed instance and if the instance base directory is on shared
storage, e.g. NFS or Ceph, between the source and destination host, the
instance base directory is incorrectly deleted.

This adds a check to see if the instance is volume-backed when checking
to see if the instance base directory should be removed from the source
host when confirming a resize.

Change-Id: I29fac80d08baf64bf69e54cf673e55123174de2a
Closes-Bug: #1728603

commit_message:
Change Amphora flavor from public to private

In octavia, when create specified nova flavor for Amphora,
it's supposed to be accessed by octavia for creating Amphora instances,
and other projetcs/users shouldn't get this flavor[1].

[1] https://github.com/openstack/octavia/blob/master/devstack/plugin.sh#L396

Closes-Bug: #1729450
Change-Id: I1d2b74dd99d949263e24b62c427c8718ec8de5b0

commit_message:
Explicitly set REVIEW_RELEASE on master

REVIEW_RELEASE defaults to STABLE_RELEASE in tripleo.sh, but for
master upgrade jobs we don't want that.  For stable to stable
upgrades we explicitly set both variables, but on master we rely
on the tripleo.sh default, which is wrong.  We should also set
REVIEW_RELEASE explicitly on stable to master upgrade jobs.

This also adds REVIEW_RELEASE to deploy.env.  I'm not positive it's
necessary, but the intent is that deploy.env represents all of the
variables needed for the deployment so it should be there.

Reverts the change in Ib70130e81fd10907cbba666c7daa86491a8a3eed as
that changes the behavior of tripleo.sh for local use.

Change-Id: I47e99e30aa189cf4075d328cd4b40429892e0ef3
Closes-Bug: 1677062

commit_message:
Capture more of the bmc console log

I've seen some IPMI errors in jobs lately, but the console log we
capture from the bmc doesn't indicate any problems.  In case that's
because we just aren't capturing enough, this patch removes the
tail call so we save the entire console log.

We may want to revert this in the interest of te-broker storage
space after we've tracked down the problem, but we should be good
to run this way for a while at least.

Change-Id: I7fadc2261e8a938b8e353bb23fcca567c628eef0

Can we disable client-side validation only if SSO is selected?'}, {'account_id': 8482, 'date': '2017-10-31 11:54:38.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

> Can we disable client-side validation only if SSO is selected?

I think that would be great, and if you have a suggestion for how to fix the javascript to do that I would be happy to try. Disabling it entirely was what Ying Zuo suggested here: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/491743/'}, {'account_id': 11885, 'date': '2017-11-01 18:51:24.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2

novalidate just disables the html5 validation that we don't need, so I think this fix is good."}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2017-11-01 21:25:40.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

Ying, this patch disables all client-side validation on the login page, not just HTML5 validation.

We don't have custom validation for required fields in JS for the login form.

If we add 'novalidate' attribute to the form, browsers will ignore 'required' attributes for inputs. In such case if 'user' or 'password' field is empty, Login button will submit the form to the server. It leads to unnecessary server load and slower feedback to a user that user/password was not entered. It makes our US worse.

I agree that we've got an issue with SSO, but I don't think that disabling client-side validation is a right way to fix this bug."}, {'account_id': 11885, 'date': '2017-11-01 21:59:51.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

 > 
 > I agree that we've got an issue with SSO, but I don't think that
 > disabling client-side validation is a right way to fix this bug.

The validation is done with Django form validation, so the request still needs to be sent. When the required fields are missing, the error message "This field is required" should be shown below the form field. With the client-side validation, a small yellow tooltip is shown for the missing required field.'}, {'account_id': 1736, 'date': '2017-11-02 15:44:02.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

I understand that we still have server-side validation but IMO client-side validation has own benefits too.

Unfortunately, I'm not familiar SSO things good enough to propose a better solution so I just leave -1 whit all my previous comments.

Core team can still merge this patch with my -1. It's not blocking"}, {'account_id': 8482, 'date': '2017-11-02 17:26:46.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Abandoning in favor of https://review.openstack.org/#/c/517382/'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2017-10-30 20:11:06.000000000', 'message': "Stop client-side validation of login form

When allowed to perform HTML5 form validation, browsers use the
'required' attribute of form fields to prevalidate input. This causes a
problem when WebSSO is enabled and the user selects an authentication
format that doesn't use a username and password field. In this case, the
fields are still labeled 'required' but are not visible to the user, and
so attempting to submit the form results in a validation error even
though the input is valid. This patch adds the novalidate tag to the
login form to disable client-side validation. The server-side validation
is smarter about which fields are really required, and still produces
correct error messages if the user selects credential authentication but
leaves the username and password fields empty.

Change-Id: Ie2fa75fedaf37cb22cabac0aec1d28583b2a177c
Closes-bug: #1703109
"}]
commit_message:
Stop client-side validation of login form

When allowed to perform HTML5 form validation, browsers use the
'required' attribute of form fields to prevalidate input. This causes a
problem when WebSSO is enabled and the user selects an authentication
format that doesn't use a username and password field. In this case, the
fields are still labeled 'required' but are not visible to the user, and
so attempting to submit the form results in a validation error even
though the input is valid. This patch adds the novalidate tag to the
login form to disable client-side validation. The server-side validation
is smarter about which fields are really required, and still produces
correct error messages if the user selects credential authentication but
leaves the username and password fields empty.

Change-Id: Ie2fa75fedaf37cb22cabac0aec1d28583b2a177c
Closes-bug: #1703109

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Included is the backport of https://review.openstack.org/515376

Change-Id: Iab55d542ec8cb3e8a26216977b4aabbda25a6c86

commit_message:
Modify ARP responder behavior from configuration

Make ARP responder able to reply to all IP addresses or only for gateway
depending on configuration

Submitted on behalf of a third-party: Orange

commit_message:
Use generic user for both zuul v2 and v3

Zuul v2 uses 'jenkins' as user, but Zuul v3 uses 'zuul'.
Using $USER solves it for both cases.

Change-Id: I7e3ca8fa9a48f3308dec46eda4ccf7e76d7b6338

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: Id21c6f19f835a3349fbd666d64babb609d3b7243

commit_message:
Run tripleo projects in tripleo gate queue

We noticed that there were a few tripleo projects that were not properly
being included in the tripleo queue. This change updates the following
projects to run in the tripleo queue.

instack-undercloud
os-apply-config
os-collect-config
os-net-config
os-refresh-config
python-tripleoclient
puppet-tripleo

Change-Id: I49b8f53a45440d861cb57d0b7cdbc30ea16c7ca2

commit_message:
Improve event streaming with a better Octavia verison

In a newer Octavia version we can specify the transport_url for
the event streamer which listens on the neutron rabbit vhost.
This configures that and also enables provisonal status streaming by
default.

Depends-On: I00422b93d3ecfb672e967c2019424b64bc44ba66

Change-Id: I8bee145d5517c66c95bb24ba62cf6f7ed497df2d

commit_message:
Rework r10k verbose option

The command "r10k puppetfile install -v" fails with:
Unrecognized options: verbose.

Rework the command to be compatible with the r10k 1.1.4.

Closes-bug: #1707629

Change-Id: I05d888125284d2808fb248e52afc95ab2b948353
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bogdando@mail.ru>
(cherry picked from commit 885abd1ae0f604fae73fe262493d3b5598613cd0)

commit_message:
Add Puppet package to bindep, for module build

We need Puppet package deployed from bindep so we can
run puppet module build with the new zuul v3 job.

Change-Id: I96df8a39bcfcd0cfad961f618ae302f5902444ea

commit_message:
Revert "Don't run sync in upgrades"

Swift fails to deploy when using >1 storage node. The fact `need_sync`
was being set using information from ansible_local in an effort to
support rolling uprades sometime in the future. Sadly this variable
causes storage nodes to be removed from the key sync which results in a
failed build. If we decide serialized rolling uprades are required for
swift we can revisit this however until then we need to remove this
constraint and ensure we're allowing successfule deployments and
upgrades of swift.

This reverts commit 176452bebf7e1ceabd2cf72a89c558c0fc7f1420.

Change-Id: I21318d7c737c2415ef760b46176c3f9b372bb634

commit_message:
Use generic user for both zuul v2 and v3

Zuul v2 uses 'jenkins' as user, but Zuul v3 uses 'zuul'.
Using $USER solves it for both cases.

Change-Id: Ib83267ef75f91fb8f95af312d644ebe19c6307c9

[{'created': '2017-10-20 15:41:56.000000000', 'message': 'Add missing puppet configuration to undercloud deploy

For containerized underclouds, the docker-puppet tool expects
symlinks created for puppet modules by specific paths.
Ensure the client creates those instead of relying on multiple
external places, like quickstart or cuztom bash scripts or docs.

Related-bug: #1682179
Closes-bug: #1725329

Change-Id: I60255386051b80c2fcacb4770e079fd450074c53
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Add missing puppet configuration to undercloud deploy

For containerized underclouds, the docker-puppet tool expects
symlinks created for puppet modules by specific paths.
Ensure the client creates those instead of relying on multiple
external places, like quickstart or cuztom bash scripts or docs.

Related-bug: #1723003
Closes-bug: #1725329

Change-Id: I60255386051b80c2fcacb4770e079fd450074c53
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bdobreli@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Merge project-config linter jobs (1/2)

The new ansible lint job works fine, merge the two linter job
and use openstack-zuul-jobs-linters like we do in other config repos.

Since project-config is not self-testing, we need to do this in two
steps.

Change-Id: I6632cce0c80c61171648d5404986ae5f23228d75

commit_message:
Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

Zuul now supports including the file extension on the playbook path
and omitting the extension is now deprecrated.  Update references
to include the extension.

commit_message:
base: use new Linaro repo

During Linaro Connect we decided to create separate repository for Kolla
project requirements. And only for those.

Repository contains:

- libvirt 3.6.0
- qemu 2.10-rc
- dpdk 17.05.2
- openvswitch 2.8.0 (with dpdk support)

Old repository is still available but just for backward compatibility.

Based on change-Id: I40f6b5e58c3c30f2b01b1f1cd5f275cd96a198a3 (instead
of cherry-pick) because Pike has own repo.

Change-Id: I31449599cc40552ed7db704a38dcc31ee80ffcb4

Upgrade rhel_reg_sat_repo to 6.2

commit_message:
RHSM: do not use retry to deploy katello-agent

katello-agent is an optional package, we don't want to use retry.
The package is available or not.

Fixing a regression from https://review.openstack.org/#/c/386529
Since we use "| true", we can't really use "retry" here.

Change-Id: Id8cd9ac54e158ee1743b2f72b169b3a066f69168
Closes-Bug: #1728614
(cherry picked from commit d9f7b01c6c21b306005bad12fcab103b0a9e7591)

commit_message:
RHSM: do not use retry to deploy katello-agent

katello-agent is an optional package, we don't want to use retry.
The package is available or not.

Fixing a regression from https://review.openstack.org/#/c/386529
Since we use "| true", we can't really use "retry" here.

Change-Id: Id8cd9ac54e158ee1743b2f72b169b3a066f69168
Closes-Bug: #1728614
(cherry picked from commit d9f7b01c6c21b306005bad12fcab103b0a9e7591)

i'm fairly certain this is failing due to a new ansible issue with version 2.4.0.

http://logs.openstack.org/07/508307/28/check/legacy-tripleo-ci-centos-7-containers-multinode/9e5b95c/logs/undercloud/home/zuul/ansible_steps.log.txt.gz

I filed a new ansible issue:

https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/32196

commit_message:
fs10: deploy steps with ansible

On FS10, use Ansible to deploy TripleO steps.
For that, it will generate Ansible configuration, download it and
execute it from the undercloud.

Depends-On: I2aa1a04ea8a963b9c613008c12b1efffd365ceaf
Change-Id: Ib7451f59664380d437a9f42efdfad09d070e8072

Deprecate standalone_network_plugin_ip_version

parameter.  It was deprecated for removal in manila proper in
Pike [1] when IPv6 support was added for network plugins.

[1] I96d3389262e9829b8b4344870cdf5c76abd22828

commit_message:
Simplify the logic of validate_network_port

osl.utils provides method is_valid_port to check port, we can
leverage it to make code more clear. Note that the code here was
incorrect in accepting 1-65535, and this change fixes it to also
include 0.

Change-Id: I60cb36a042fd808edca66b07d7248213debd4dff

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Change-Id: I565fdf75e03fdc1c1296b39f8cff206c7eeccb9a

commit_message:
Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

Zuul now supports including the file extension on the playbook path
and omitting the extension is now deprecrated.  Update references
to include the extension.

Change-Id: I3f43e9a4593d8b27de25bf2140b467e1351f3792

commit_message:
Functional regression test for evacuate with a target

In I6ddcaaca37fc5387c2d2e9f51c67ea9e85acb5c5 we forgot to update the
legacy filter properties dictionary so the requested target wasn't
passed to the scheduler when evacuating.
Adding a functional test for verifying the behaviour.

NOTE(sbauza): The issue has been incendentally fixed in Pike by
I434af8e4ad991ac114dd67d66797a562d16bafe2 so the regression test just
verifies that the expected behaviour works.
The Newton and Ocata backports will be slightly different from that one as we
need to verify that host3 will be preferred eventually over host2.

Related-Bug: #1702454

Change-Id: Id9adb10d2ef821c8b61d8f1d5dc9dd66ec7aaac8

commit_message:
Enable network-spaces for swift-storage relation

Ensure that any network space binding provided by the end user
is used as units join the swift-storage relation.

This allows backend communication to swift-storage units to be
network isolated from frontend public access to the swift
deployment.

Change-Id: If29ba3dfb1379f0cda20d9685e654d911d67df1d
Closes-Bug: 1697491

commit_message:
Use db transactions when error-finish is called

Multiple spots were not using DB transactions when processing error
transitions:

  node_info.fsm_event(istate.Events.error)
  node_info.finished(error='Oops!')

which led to race conditions.

The patch replaces these racy calls with a refactored version of
NodeInfo.finished(), that expects an error event as an argument, upon
which the (terminal) error state should be navigated to.

Change-Id: I0bb051d1956a996ed006d55a5ca2d670d9455047
Closes-Bug: #1721233
Closes-Bug: #1721230

Make _abort set error and finished_at in fms_event

TL;DR the fsm_transition decorator has no chance to update anything else
besides the node_info state attribute.  As a result, discrepancies such as
in the bug below could have been observed in an HA inspector deployment.

This patch moves the node_info.finished() and the
node_info.fsm_event(abort) into a single DB transaction to avoid the
discrepancies.

Closes-Bug: #1723384

Fix state discrepancy in process._finish

The _finish calls node_info.finished() inside while being decorated to
perform a 'finish' state transition, that sets node_info._state = finished
right after the _finish returns.  Therefore a window of state discrepancy
between the node_info.finished() and the node_info._state exists.

This patch closes that window by putting them into a single DB
transaction.

Change-Id: I59211885bfec9a9e28a6bc636e0f35ac85eaba23

[{'created': '2017-10-24 22:57:18.000000000', 'message': "Make _abort set error and finished_at in fms_event

TL;DR the fsm_transition decorator had no chance to update anything else
besides the node_info state attribute.  As a result, races such as in the
bug below could have been observed in an HA inspector deployment.

Now it is possible to pass the fsm_transition decorator kwargs onto the
fms_evet, to be committed together with the state transition in a single
transaction.

This allows one to decorate a fsm_transition in such a way as to pass
error='Canceled by operator', finished=True and finished_at =
timeutils.utcnow() onto the fsm_event to be committed together with the
state update.

The fsm_transition-decorated _abort was decorated exactly in that way to
allow the fsm_transition to update those fields upon the state change.

Change-Id: I54756b4285939b7e9c4895106a99410e06e1ee2f
Closes-Bug: #1723384

commit_message:
Make _abort set error and finished_at in fms_event

TL;DR the fsm_transition decorator has no chance to update anything else
besides the node_info state attribute.  As a result, discrepancies such as
in the bug below could have been observed in an HA inspector deployment.

This patch moves the node_info.finished() and the
node_info.fsm_event(finish) into a single DB transaction to avoid the
discrepancies.

Change-Id: I54756b4285939b7e9c4895106a99410e06e1ee2f
Closes-Bug: #1723384

commit_message:
Relax background introspection abort processing

The introspecion _abort function is decorated as a strictly non-reentrant
state transition, which is a bit of an overkill.

The reason for it being a strict transition was to be able to put the node
introspection into an error state no matter either a cache discrepancy or
an invalid state transition.

This patch relaxes the precondition to only check state transition
validity and apply the transition but drops the ability to put the
introspection into the error state immediately.

Closes-Bug #1721536

Change-Id: Ie3d9faa175852ab772a7ed644a8328f7a4d07e92

commit_message:
Catch node state errors in fsm_transition

The ordering of decortators was wrong. As a result, both the
NodeStateRaceCondition and NodeStateInvalidEvent were leaking to the node
state instead of being reported to the user.

The legitimate use case of those exceptions being introspection error
causes are only in strict (non-reentrant) transitions.

Change-Id: If3c978b178fc9ee2f6c5342a1f399980d0450b41
Related-Bug: #1721536
Related-Bug: #1721512

commit_message:
Stop registering "graphs" resource to quota

As it's a POST-only special purpose resource, quota doesn't
make much sense.  Even worse, it prevents the new quota_details
extension from working if lbaas is configured.

Closes-Bug: #1715594
Change-Id: I9bc85c9bab1fba1ae54259cde6f34f6b8d43b4a9

commit_message:
Rework r10k verbose option

The command "r10k puppetfile install -v" fails with:
Unrecognized options: verbose.

Rework the command to be compatible with the r10k 1.1.4.

Closes-bug: #1707629

Change-Id: I05d888125284d2808fb248e52afc95ab2b948353
Signed-off-by: Bogdan Dobrelya <bogdando@mail.ru>

commit_message:
Only enable keystone notifications if telemetry is enabled

This will get rid of the unnecessary notifications that were being
produced and help with the undercloud's memory consumption.

Change-Id: If4d97e5069ca678edbcd2270a75f6faf67364420
Closes-Bug: #1729293

Currently a bind is used when mounting /dev/pts in the chroot.

commit_message:
Use -t devpts for /dev/pts mounts

Currently a bind is used when mounting /dev/pts in chroot.
This leads to problems - especially when running DIB in parallel:
It was observed that the /dev/pts mount vanishes from the host
system.

This patch uses '-t devpts' - as it is done for /sys and /proc -
for handling /dev/pts.

Change-Id: Id7775ae6fca6502af800e7b73a00862ef320206b
Signed-off-by: Andreas Florath <andreas@florath.net>

Add kube_dashboard_enabled label to user guide

Following the introduction of the kubernetes dashboard deployment, add to the
user guide the label to be used to disable/enable this feature.

It's enabled by default.

Closes-Bug: #1718608

subject: Make possible to use ansible 2.4
revisions:
[{'created': '2017-11-02 13:54:19.000000000', 'message': "Make possible to use ansible 2.4

Ansible 2.4 has changed the interface for var plugins.
Our vars plugin shouldn't be used in ansible 2.4, because the
features we were looking for are now standard.

However the plugin is still shipped. So we need to ensure
this vars plugin doesn't get loaded on ansible 2.4.

Ansible will not load a vars plugin in its plugin location
if no VarsModule is defined. This commit abuses this
mechanism to conditionally load the vars module depending on
the version, at the expense of throwing a warning in
Ansible 2.4.

Change-Id: I5119f043747044dfd5f556475b5618b6805f7b85
"}]
commit_message:
Make possible to use ansible 2.4

Ansible 2.4 has changed the interface for var plugins.
Our vars plugin shouldn't be used in ansible 2.4, because the
features we were looking for are now standard.

However the plugin is still shipped. So we need to ensure
this vars plugin doesn't get loaded on ansible 2.4.

Ansible will not load a vars plugin in its plugin location
if no VarsModule is defined. This commit abuses this
mechanism to conditionally load the vars module depending on
the version, at the expense of throwing a warning in
Ansible 2.4.

Change-Id: I5119f043747044dfd5f556475b5618b6805f7b85

I understand this problem. It seems that in the environment where neutron is used to provide the network, network_label_regex is set to. *, And ^ private $ is used in other network environments. I was thinking about whether this would need to be changed, and in the puppet deployment environment, the value was modified during the deployment process. Which in itself depends only on whether the user has used nova-network or neutron.Keep watch and discuss'}, {'account_id': 26311, 'date': '2017-10-26 08:00:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

recheck'}, {'account_id': 13562, 'date': '2017-11-01 16:59:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-2

This code should not merge.

The bug was marked invalid by Amrith before it was reopened for this proposed fix.  The issue is occurring because of a misconfiguration of Trove.  The fix is to properly configure the network_label_regex config property, not to completely open it up with .*.

The one fix I could see for this bug is what was suggested in the bug description, check for None and raise a better error message than index out of range.'}, {'account_id': 13562, 'date': '2017-11-01 18:13:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

I made a mistake.  I still hold this is a configuration issue. However, the sample conf does document that the value should be set to .* when you are using Neutron.

Nova-network is deprecated.  So these changes could probably go in and resolve common configuration errors.

The bug should still be invalidated, the commit message should not list it as closes, and the commit message should say this change is to change the default configuration value because Nova network (the current value), is deprecated.'}, {'account_id': 26311, 'date': '2017-11-02 02:15:47.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Published edit on patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 26311, 'date': '2017-11-02 02:17:23.000000000', 'content': 'Topic bug/1627565 removed'}, {'account_id': 22694, 'date': '2017-11-02 03:19:23.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

bot script using our exclude list.

commit_message:
Remove new retired projects from update bot

Update bot should not try to update repos that have been retired.
os_freezer being newly retired, we exclude it from the proposal
bot script using our exclude list.

commit_message:
Add retry loop for docker pull

The prepare command also needs a retry loop for docker pull in order to
accommodate with the not so infrequent I/O failures.

Fetch Cinder availability zones list for volume creation

We have to fetch and show Cinder availability zones list during volume
creation and volume creation from image.

commit_message:
Zuul: add file extension to playbook path

Zuul now supports including the file extension on the playbook path
and omitting the extension is now deprecrated.  Update references
to include the extension.

Change-Id: I3af2e786ac17b039147de3560aa2fa8cee4c83cd

commit_message:
Make memcached logs verbosity configurable

This adds the MemcachedDebug flag which makes memcached logs verbose.
Also, the service now reacts to the global Debug flag.

Related-Bug: #1720183
Change-Id: Ie8120359a12f734aad584b083c8362dd21b70dea
(cherry picked from commit 85234209307e5917be40ca78342617d003429858)

commit_message:
Add Federation API specification

Add a new spec covering the impact and implementation details for a new
Magnum API managing federation and federated clusters.

Implements: blueprint federation-api
Co-Authored-By: Clenimar Filemon <clenimar.filemon@gmail.com>

Change-Id: I1b58f44520c6d968dd0c930a54dbd0ef36c2cb4e

commit_message:
Initial OSA zuul v3 role jobs

This patch implements an initial set of jobs intended to match
the current job execution method. It does not intend to improve
how the jobs are executed - only to replicate what is currently
in openstack-infra/openstack-zuul-jobs and provide the platform
to iterate on.

Co-Authored-By: Jean-Philippe Evrard <jean-philippe@evrard.me>
Change-Id: I4aa7591c931501490e706b9d61ba0bc12c006baa
(cherry picked from commit 0147d155d467f8dfbe3820e92cd9bd657b8d4974)

commit_message:
Disable MongoDB in scenario002

We have disabled mongo by default in containers via:

Id2e6550fb7c319fc52469644ea022cf35757e0ce Disable mongodb by default
Ie09ce2a52128eef157e4d768c1c4776fc49f2324 Containerized mongodb, disable by default, fix upgrade

Let's not use it in scenario002 either.

NB: Not entirely clean cherry-pick due to scenario002-multinode-containers.yaml
    having many more services in master than in pike.

Change-Id: I0d2df25ed797ffb8425ba81736526d3688e5de5c
Closes-Bug: #1724679
(cherry picked from commit 900416d9809bf4446c0c037128edb033ab9b3bcc)

commit_message:
Switch to use keystone v3

Keystone v2 api's are removed in [1], so it's required
to use keystone v3 otherwise all requests fallbacks to
keystone v2.0 and fails.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/499783/

Change-Id: Ie2794d5fb12785e7c620c4ec8e3ccc2fb64d9e3b
Closes-Bug: #1723838

commit_message:
Fix usage of _log_deprecation_warnings

As Consuming projects should fix deprecation warnings
_log_deprecation_warnings in oslo.context is deprecated
in version '2.6' and will be removed in version '3.0'.

Change-Id: If5f682c5141abf6dd9f8268abd83b3d204b18ec3

commit_message:
Use handlers to restart services and move dnsmasq to a unit file

These changes further optimise the lxc_host role so that it's using more
of the built in modules and making better use of handlers.

Moving the dnsmasq process to a unit file gives operators the ability to
restart the dnsmasq process if there's an issue with the service. It
also ensures the service stays running as systemd will take better care
of the service by isolating it within a specific cgroup, ensuring good
reporting and memory management, and providing the ability to recover
from failures in an automated way.

Closes-Bug: #1518485
Change-Id: I42d0caa3b12e70a3601c30051eefc067e81a71bb
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
